Package: herald
Title: CDISC Conformance Validation for Clinical Trial Submissions
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Vignesh", "", email = "about.vignesh@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Pure-R conformance validation for CDISC clinical data
    submissions. Checks SDTM and ADaM datasets against published CDISC
    Library conformance rules, controlled terminology, and Define-XML 2.1
    specifications. Produces submission-ready findings reports (HTML,
    XLSX, JSON) with rule-level provenance linked to CDISC source. Ships
    a first-class Define-XML 2.1 authoring object with full read, edit,
    and write roundtrip (semantic preservation). Designed for teams
    running reproducible pipelines with 'renv', 'targets', and CI --
    a 'CRAN'-clean, R-native alternative to Java-based desktop
    validators.
